Package game.mission

Class Mission

java.lang.Object
game.mission.Mission
All Implemented Interfaces:
IMission
public class Mission extends Object implements IMission
Represents a mission in the game. The Mission class follows the Singleton design pattern, ensuring that only one instance of a mission exists during runtime.

    • initialize

      public static void initialize(String missionCode, int version, Player player, Target target, ArrayUnorderedList<Enemy> enemies, ArrayUnorderedList<Item> items, Map missionMap, ArrayUnorderedList<Room> entriesAndExits)
      Initializes or updates the singleton instance of the Mission class with the provided data.
      Parameters:
      missionCode - The unique identifier for the mission.
      version - The version of the mission.
      player - The player associated with this mission.
      target - The target the player must achieve in this mission.
      enemies - The list of enemies in the mission.
      items - The list of items available in the mission.
      missionMap - The map of the mission.
      entriesAndExits - The list of rooms that are the entries and exits for the mission.
